In an eloquent last chapter, written as Capps was waging her final battle with cancer, they turn to "unfinished narratives," those stories that will never have a comprehensible end. With a hybrid perspective--part humanities, part social science--their book captures these complexities and fathoms the intricate and potent narratives that live within and among us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDiscourse analysis, Narrative. 0aStorytelling. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aCapps, Lisa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674041592?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674041592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674041592/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK